        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Fail closed when Slack mention detection is unavailable",
        "body": "## Summary\nFixes Slack mention gating so channels that require a mention do not accept ordinary messages when explicit mention detection is unavailable.\n\nThis can happen when `auth.test` fails during Slack monitor startup, leaving `botUserId` empty until restart. The previous behavior treated that as `canDetectMention=false` and allowed the message through even when `requireMention=true`.\n\n## Changes\n- Fail closed when mention detection is unavailable and a mention is required\n- Add a specific Slack drop reason and log context for detection-unavailable skips\n- Make the Slack startup warning clearer when `auth.test` fails\n- Add/update regression tests for the fail-closed behavior\n\n## Verification\n- `git diff --check`\n\nVitest was not run locally because this sandbox does not have `node` or `pnpm` available.",
